//HTML provides the structure of a webpage, while CSS provides its design and appearance.


Why Do We Use CSS?

Makes web pages attractive and visually appealing.
Separates content (HTML) from design (CSS).
Reduces code duplication by applying the same styles to multiple elements.
Makes websites easier to maintain and update.
Helps create responsive designs that work on different screen sizes.

